oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: E. F. Falconnet
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Head and shoulders portrait of a bearded E. F. Falconnet.

Born Eugene Louis Frederic de Freudeureich Falconnet in Berne, Switzerland, Falconnet adopted the name "E. F. Falconnet" in 1852. He later served in the Confederate Army during the Civil War and was also an inventor, engineer, geologist and composer.
